# RBK Command Center Update
### A Custom Dashboard Built for Rabbi Krauss

---

## The Big Picture

After our last meeting, I decided to pivot away from the off-the-shelf tools (Monday.com, Zapier) and build a **completely custom experience** designed specifically around your workflow. The result is the **RBK Command Center** — a single dashboard where you and Emily can manage your inbox, calendar, tasks, and meeting agenda all in one place.

**Why the pivot?** The generic tools weren't flexible enough. You needed something that works the way *you* work — not the other way around.

**Where we are now:** The core app is built, functional, and processing real emails. Emily and I have been testing and refining it together.

---

## What It Does Today

### Email Triage — Automated & Organized
- Emails are **pulled automatically** from your inbox every 5 minutes
- **AI categorizes each email** into priority buckets so you see what matters first:
  - **RBK Action** — Needs your direct response
  - **Emily Action** — Emily can handle
  - **Invitations & Meeting Invites** — Events and RSVPs
  - **Important (No Action)** — Worth knowing, no reply needed
  - **Review** — Documents/materials to look at
  - **FYI** — Informational only
- **AI drafts replies** for emails that need a response
- Emily reviews and edits drafts, marks them ready, you approve, and they send — all from the dashboard

### Calendar — At a Glance
- Today's schedule displayed on the dashboard with **one-click join buttons** for Zoom/Meet/Teams
- Browse previous and upcoming days
- Create or delete events right from the dashboard
- Add calendar events directly from an email

### Tasks & Meeting Agenda
- Create tasks from emails, assign to you or Emily
- Flag emails to discuss at your next meeting
- Track what's done and what's still open

### Quick Access Panel
- **Important Docs** — Links to your most-used documents (editable)
- **Quick Links** — Today's Folder, Daily Announcements, Daily Folder
- **Drafts Ready** counter — See at a glance how many replies are waiting for your approval

